</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4371/logout-with-modshifte-discards-unsafed-documents-how-to-avoid-this/?comment=4411#comment-4411</link><description>Got it. I3 has already the solution. For a clean shutdown of i.e. firefox and a subsequent logout:
i3-msg '[class="firefox"] kill;
sleep 1;
i3-msg 'exit'</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 Aug 2014 21:01:04 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4371/logout-with-modshifte-discards-unsafed-documents-how-to-avoid-this/?comment=4411#comment-4411</guid></item><item><title>Comment by KJ44 for &lt;p&gt;To get Gnome &lt;em&gt;Desktop Environment&lt;/em&gt; behaviour from i3 &lt;em&gt;Window Manager&lt;/em&gt; I'd suggest experimenting with a script that calls 'gnome-session-save' or similar. It might "just work" but you might have to start various Gnome daemons and the like to get it all to work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://linuxg.net/shutdown-reboot-logout-ubuntu-13-04-system-with-the-gnome-session-quit-command/"&gt;http://linuxg.net/shutdown-reboot-log...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

