 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4371/logout-with-modshifte-discards-unsafed-documents-how-to-avoid-this/?answer=4376#post-id-4376</link><description>Don't rely on a machine to remind you not to throw your work away. Computers are stupid, and while they can be made to do some wonderful things, time spent trying to make them do someting smart might be better spent learning good work habits.

Every time you make a change to a document, save it. Full stop. Even if (for whatever reason) you don't save every single time you make a change you shouldn't give yourself the opportunity to forget that you have unsaved work. [Avoid multitasking like the plague](http://www.npr.org/2013/05/10/182861382/the-myth-of-multitasking). It's pointless. Finish what's important and then move on to the next task.</description><pubDate>Sun, 03 Aug 2014 16:28:56 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4371/logout-with-modshifte-discards-unsafed-documents-how-to-avoid-this/?answer=4376#post-id-4376</guid></item></channel></rss>